|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/16/2356254           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

In the IT trench writes "How's this for a new twist on the old
responsible disclosure debate? Hackers are using clues from Microsoft's
pre-patch security advisories to [0]create and publish proof-of-concept
exploits. The latest zero-day flaw in the Windows DNS Server RPC
interface implementation is a perfect example of the tug-o-war within the
Microsoft Security Response Center about how much information should be
included in the pre-patch advisory."

