| Chimps Evolved More Than Humans                                    |
|   from the our-chimp-overlords dept.                               |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday April 17, @17:44 (It's funny.  Laugh|
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/17/2018225      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

jas_public writes "Since the human and chimp families split about 6
million years ago, [0]chimpanzee genes seem to have evolved more than
human genes. The results, detailed in the Proceedings of the National
Academy of Sciences, go against the conventional wisdom that humans are
the result of a high degree of genetic selection, evidenced by our
relatively large brains, cognitive abilities, and bipedalism. The
researchers found that 'substantially more genes in chimps evolved in
ways that were beneficial than was the case with human genes.'"

