| Google To Add Presentations                                        |
|   from the looking-office-like dept.                               |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday April 17, @19:56 (Google)           |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/17/2157217              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

A number of readers (some from the audience at Web 2.0 Expo) wrote to let
us know that [0]Google is adding presentations to their Docs and
Spreadsheets package. With the announcement the company revealed that
they have purchased [1]Tonic Systems to help with the new presentation
software. It's expected to be ready by summer. Google's CEO Eric Schmidt
was [2]asked if Docs and Spreadsheets will compete with MS Office, and he
said, "We don't think so. It doesn't have all the functionality, nor is
it intended to have the functionality of products like Microsoft Office."

